Messi’s incredible MLS contract explained ⚽️

Messi declined a highly profitable proposal from Saudi Arabia and opted not to reunite with his former club Barcelona, citing apprehensions about their financial circumstances.

Messi’s agreement is set to bring him a staggering $54 million per year, securing his position as the top earner in Major League Soccer (MLS).

However, his salary is just the beginning. The contract entails Messi also receiving a portion of Apple and Adidas’ revenue in the form of shares.

The MLS operates a streaming package on Apple TV that requires viewers to pay a fee in order to access all the games. Following his arrival, Messi is now poised to receive a portion of the revenue generated from these subscriptions.

According to sources, Messi has reportedly been presented with a profit-sharing arrangement that would entitle him to a portion of the earnings generated by Adidas as a result of his involvement in the MLS. Adidas serves as the official supplier of kits to all 29 teams in the MLS, in addition to being the footwear and ball sponsor.

According to ESPN reports, it has been indicated that Messi is being presented with an opportunity to acquire partial ownership of an MLS team once his contract concludes.

Ronaldo Nazário - The Phenomenon Was an Absolute Monster!

Ronaldo Nazario, often referred to as Ronaldo R9, is a retired footballer renowned for his striking abilities. He represented the Brazil national team and made significant contributions during his career at Inter Milan and Real Madrid

Ronaldo’s remarkable achievements include being honored as the FIFA World Player of the Year on three occasions and securing two Ballon d’Or awards.

The commencement of Ronaldo’s professional club career took place in 1994 with PSV. Swiftly, he emerged as one of Europe’s finest young talents, showcasing his prowess by netting an impressive 30 goals in 33 appearances during his debut season with the club.

His exceptional performances led to him receiving the prestigious Ballon d’Or accolade in both 1997 and 2002. Additionally, Ronaldo played a pivotal role in Inter’s triumph in the UEFA Cup of 1998, contributing with 59 goals in 99 appearances for the club.

In 2002, Ronaldo’s talents earned him a historic transfer to Real Madrid for a world-record fee of €46 million. His impact was immediate, as he found the back of the net 30 times in his inaugural season, aiding Real Madrid in capturing the UEFA Champions League title in 2003.

On the international stage, Ronaldo played a crucial part in Brazil’s victorious campaign at the 2002 World Cup in South Korea and Japan. He showcased his scoring prowess by registering eight goals throughout the tournament, including a brace in the final against Germany. As a result, Ronaldo claimed the Golden Boot award as the tournament’s top scorer.

THE MOST EXPENSIVE FOOTBALL PLAYER EVER

Who holds the title of the most expensive football player ever?

Currently, the title of the most expensive football player ever is held by Neymar, who made a move from Barcelona to PSG in 2017 for a record-breaking transfer fee of $252 million.

Could Kylian Mbappé become the new most expensive player?

Kylian Mbappé, the talented French football star, has been the subject of significant speculation about his future. Recently, there were reports that he turned down an enormous annual salary offer of $221 million from Al Hilal, which could have been worth up to $776 million. According to transfer expert Fabrizio Romano, Mbappé refused to negotiate with the club.

Despite Al Hilal’s tempting offer, it appears that Mbappé has his sights set on a move to Real Madrid in 2024. Al Hilal is reportedly aware of Mbappé’s intentions and is even willing to offer him a one-year deal in an attempt to secure his services.

If Kylian Mbappé ultimately decides to join Al Hilal and completes the transfer, it would shatter the existing record and become the most expensive transfer in football history, surpassing Neymar’s record-setting move to PSG in 2017.

SILVIO BERLUSCONI FOOTBALL PREDICTION IN 2007 COMES TRUE

Silvio Berlusconi, the late Italian Prime Minister and ex-owner of AC Milan, who died at the age of 86, was a visionary and influential figure in the world of football. 

Berlusconi transformed AC Milan into a European powerhouse, winning 8 Serie A titles and 5 Champions League trophies during his 31-year reign.

The tycoon also foresaw the future of football back in 2007, when he made a prophetic statement about the decline of Serie A and the rise of the English Premier League and the Arab investors

In an interview with La Gazzetta dello Sport back in November 2007, Berlusconi said, “I see Serie A getting more and more poor. We’re leaders now but in 15 years we’ll be a supermarket. The EPL will be the number one league with everyone else behind them. Then the Arabs will come into football and we don’t have any appeal anymore. There’s no infrastructure or new stadiums. We’re still behind by 30 years.”

Berlusconi foresaw the future of football and the Italian management has since done nothing to improve the league.

Canada planning framework to make Google & Meta pay for news. What are your thoughts 🤔??

Canada’s Online News Act, part of a global trend to make tech firms like Alphabet’s Google and Meta’s Facebook pay for news, became law in June but has not yet come into effect.

On Thursday, the Canadian regulatory body in charge of enacting the nation’s online news law announced its intention to commence the establishment of a framework for facilitating negotiations between news organizations and internet giants in the upcoming fall season.

Both companies said the law is unworkable for their businesses, and Meta has already ended news sharing on its platforms. Google also plans to block news from search results in Canada before the law comes into effect.

Neymar’s Extraordinary Contract with Al Hilal

According to reports, Neymar’s two-year contract with Al-Hilal will guaranteed him $300 million USD, and up to $400 million USD based on commercial deals with the club.

In 1984, Michael Jordan faced a critical decision about his footwear partnership. His initial inclination was to align with Adidas, despite their reluctance to grant him his own signature shoe line.

Jordan’s desire to collaborate with Adidas persisted, even though they were not prepared to offer him a unique shoe line. On the other hand, Nike was enthusiastic about providing him with a signature shoe, but Jordan’s agent, David Falk, struggled to persuade him to entertain the idea.

In a pivotal moment, Deloris, Michael Jordan’s mother, intervened and urged him to board the plane and attend the meeting with Nike. This decision proved to be a game-changer.

Nike extended a lucrative offer to Jordan, amounting to $250,000, more than double the proposal from Adidas. What’s more, they promised him his own signature shoe. Upon hearing this, Michael’s father offered some sage advice: “You’d have to be a fool not to take this deal. This is the best deal.”

With that, Jordan embraced the Nike offer, leading to the birth of his iconic signature shoe, the Air Jordan. The success that followed exceeded all expectations. Initially hoping to sell $3 million worth of Air Jordans in three years, Nike achieved an astonishing $126 million in sales.

Ever wondered 🤔 how Bank of America came to be? 🏦

Back in 1904, Amadeo Giannini founded Bank of Italy in San Francisco. 🌉 Originally, it was all about helping working-class people, especially Italian-Americans.

But then, in 1906, disaster struck when a devastating earthquake hit. 🌍 Over 80% of the city was destroyed, and most businesses crumbled, including banks.

Giannini was a true hero. He saved all his bank’s assets and records, even hiding them under layers of fruit in a wagon! 🍎🚚

After the earthquake, he put his trust in people who others had written off as credit risks. He lent money on a handshake and a smile, even to immigrants ignored by other banks. 🤝😊

Giannini  also changed the banking game by introducing branch banking, taking inspiration from Canada. 🍁 He opened multiple locations across the state, even buying up other banks.

In 1928, Bank of Italy merged with another bank, and voilà, Bank of America was born, becoming the world’s largest commercial bank! 🌎💰

Giannini was a people person. He personally visited branches, remembered everyone’s faces, and even the names of their children! 😊🏢

⚫🔵 Giuseppe Meazza’s Storia: Inter’s Legendary Footballer ⚽🇮🇹

Recognized as one of Inter’s iconic players, Giuseppe Meazza’s journey is nothing short of extraordinary. With three Serie A titles and two World Cups as Italy’s team captain, his legacy is etched in football history.

As a young dreamer, Meazza’s heart was set on AC Milan, but fate took a turn when he was turned away due to being underweight. A perceptive scout from Inter saw his potential during a street game with a ball made of rags, offering him the chance of a lifetime.

Decades ahead of his time, Meazza boasted an impressive scoring record of 241 goals in 348 games with Inter, along with 33 goals in 53 appearances for Italy. A true maestro on the field.

Despite his talent, Meazza’s love for alcohol often led to clashes with the club’s directors. Eventually, he fulfilled his dream by signing with his boyhood team, Milan. His football journey also took him to Inter’s fierce rival, Juventus, as well as Atalanta and Varese.

In a remarkable full-circle moment, Meazza returned to Inter as a player/coach, and the stadium was rightfully named after this football legend. 🌟
